OL,3,CEx-soldier who lost his leg in service
OL,4,Cand was given infected blood
OL,6,FMr West, now 63, who now lives in only
OL,7,Fdiscovered that he was infected with
OL,8,Fthe virus when he was turned away from
OL,9,Fgiving blood.
OL,11,FSubsequent tests have revealed that he
OL,12,Fhas suffered severe liver damage as a
OL,13,Fresult of the virus going undetected
OL,14,Ffor so many years.
OL,16,FHe also has to be monitored for a life-
OL,17,Fthreatening bleeding condition.
