OL,3,CEx-soldier who lost his leg in service
OL,4,Cand was given infected blood
OL,6,F"I assume the people who gave me blood
OL,7,Fwere totally unaware of the risk (of
OL,8,Finfected blood) ` I wouldn't blame
OL,9,Fsurgeons, or nurses, or whoever gave
OL,10,Fme the blood, but systematically there
OL,11,Fis obviously some blame there."
OL,13,FMr West described how he has needed
OL,14,Ffurther surgeries throughout his life,
OL,15,Fincluding two knee replacements and a
OL,16,Fhip replacement, adding: "What I find
OL,17,Finteresting is at no time was the Hep
OL,18,FC discovered in 40 odd years, I find
OL,19,Fthat really strange."
