OL,3,CEx-soldier who lost his leg in service
OL,4,Cand was given infected blood
OL,6,F"Then I had to go and be tested for
OL,7,Fthe virus and one of the specialist
OL,8,Fnurses said: 'By the looks of the
OL,9,Freading you have had this for more
OL,10,Fthan 20 years'.
OL,12,F"We then backtracked through my Army
OL,13,Fmedical records and it seems it was as
OL,14,Fa result of a blood transfusion from
OL,15,Fmy injuries."
OL,17,FTrained as a vehicle mechanic during
OL,18,Fhis time in the Army, Mr West went on
OL,19,Fto work for a large multinational
OL,20,Fcompany after he was medically
OL,21,Fdischarged.
